<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-757-744  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 757 744.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC World  Nov 1989 v7 n11 p182(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bridge/386 and Toolkit 1.1. (Software Review) (Windows: a PC Worldsupplement on windowing environments and applications.)andO;(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Walkenbach, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Softbridge Microsystems Corp's Bridge/386 and Toolkit 1.1 are twobatch-language programming tools for Microsoft Windows which areavailable either separately or as a single package.andP;  Thestand-alone versions are underpowered, but the combination packagelets users create customized menus, automatically load files, ordevelop turnkey interfaces that tie together differentapplications.andP;  Bridge/386 has a BASIC-like batch language and anintegrated editor called BRED.andP;  BRED allows the user to paste menufunctions and commands directly into a file and has a RUN commandfor testing files quickly.andP;  Single-step and line-by-line trackingmake debugging easy and Bridge can save code in Windows SDK formatfor prototyping.andP;  However, the $695 program lacks on-line help,cannot develop custom icons and is geared to developers andadvanced users.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Softbridge Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Microsoft Windows (Graphical user interface) (computer programs)Bridge-386 (Program development software)Toolkit 1.1 (Program development software).andO;Topic:     Batch ProcessingProgram Development Tools.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>